profile_positions.description:
Some of my responsibilities at Deltares include:
• Preparing and reviewing vulnerability and exposure databases for conducting flood 
risk assessments using tools such as Delft-FIAT and GIS;
• Recommending authorities to prioritise flood risk mitigation measures and developing 
flood risk strategies;
• Supporting local authorities in developing disaster risk reduction plans and disaster 
preparedness and response plans;
• Designing, implementing, and evaluating innovative approaches such as serious 
games, workshops, and citizen science;
• Designing, implementing, and evaluating inclusive stakeholder and community 
engagement and participatory approaches for flood risk projects;
• Developing capacity development programs for various target groups for flood risk 
projects;
• Developing and executing communication plans for flood risk projects;
• Collaborating with clients, key stakeholders, local authorities, and local communities 
as necessary for projects;
• Representing Deltares at conferences and presenting or organizing sessions on 
topics related to flood risk;
• Utilizing tools such as Delft-FIAT, CIrcle, and GIS within projects.

- Conducted hydrological and hydraulic analysis of the Bagmati River basin, and organized and participated in river studies and scientific data collection;
- Studied flood risk perception among communities living along the Bagmati corridor and assessed the importance of Early Warning Systems in flood risk management;
- Studied existing disaster risk management strategies in the river basin;
- Coordinated the team for river expeditions and communicated with other organizations and government officials as per project requirements.

- Analyzed the hydrological and hydraulic modeling results of the river basins for Tamor-Mewa Hydroelectric Project and Simara-Tamsariya Sector of Mechi-Mahakali Railway projects;
- Designed river training structures based on hydrology and prepared monthly progress reports, final hydrology reports, and presentation slides;
- Analyzed meteorological and hydrological data, conducted hydrological and hydraulic modeling for the study of impacts of climate change on water-induced disasters in Koshi river basin;
- Identified gaps in existing disaster risk management strategies and recommended essential improvements, and prepared progress reports, final reports, and presentation slides.
